The paper discusses the development of the SJ Framework for session-based distributed programming, which is a topic related to programming languages (cs.PL) and security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the implementation of security measures to protect communication safety at runtime, which is related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper formally proves the security properties of the extended SJ delegation protocols, which is related to distributed systems (cs.DS).
